  "texts": [
    "Furthermore, we choose weeks instead of days, as we are interested in general shifts and overall changes in behaviour over time, which are captured sufficiently well on a weekly basis.",
    "Through this weekly definition, we can dramatically reduce the size of our dataset, hence more complex modelling approaches become computationally feasible.",
    "We drop the first and last week in our dataset as these are incomplete (less than 7 days) and aggregate the remaining tweets on a weekly basis for each user and language.",
    "Finally within this, we are only considering weeks in which users are active (we define this as any week in which a user is tweeting at least once, as well as up to two weeks after), in order to account for the times in which users may be inactive for several weeks at a time or abandon their accounts.",
    "Thus, our new sample ranges from 13th January 2020 to 10th October 2022 and consists of 143 analysis weeks, 13,643 users and 1,045,245 observations."
  ],
